    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted as sufficiently documented for the current phase of development, with acknowledged gaps in model form uncertainty and use error that are flagged for resolution prior to regulatory submission. The ContextOfUse prose description references 5 flow-speed operating combinations and Class III device conditions; structured operating envelope constraints are deferred to the next assessment cycle. The overall evidence package supports a conditional acceptance with mandatory remediation actions.",
